  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Performance artiste",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will deliver engaging live performances in a fast-paced nightclub environment, collaborating with entertainment teams and following artistic direction to create memorable experiences for diverse audiences.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform live shows according to scheduled sets, ensuring high energy and audience engagement</li><li>Participate actively in themed acts, artistic segments, or choreographed performances to enhance entertainment value</li><li>Maintain grooming, punctuality, and professionalism to uphold the club’s standards</li><li>Collaborate effectively with entertainment managers, DJs, singers, and technical crew to coordinate performances</li><li>Attend rehearsals and apply artistic direction to improve show quality and consistency</li><li>Follow all club rules and comply with MOM performer regulations to ensure a safe and lawful work environment</li><li>Engage audiences appropriately while adhering to performance guidelines and maintaining a positive atmosphere</li><li>Demonstrate strong stage presence and confidence to captivate and entertain crowds</li><li>Exhibit physical stamina and discipline to sustain performance quality during late-night, weekend, and public holiday shifts</li><li>Follow choreography and show direction accurately to deliver seamless performances</li><li>Maintain a professional and responsible attitude throughout work activities</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Prior experience as a performance artist, dancer, or entertainer to contribute to performance quality</li><li>Fluency in Mandarin to facilitate communication with Mandarin-speaking clientele and staff</li></ul>",
